
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `gnome-disks` yek barname grafiki ast baraye modiriat disk-ha va drive-ha dar system-haye Linux ke az Gnome estefade mikonand. Shoma mitavanid partition-ha ra bebinid, format konid, mount/unmount konid, va S.M.A.R.T. status-ha ra check konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 az GUI estefade mikonad --> baraye karbarane tazehkar kheili rahattar ast.
    🔹 support az LVM --> LVM(Logical Volume Management) ra hemayat mikonad.
    🔹 check kardan S.M.A.R.T. status --> vaziat disk-ha ra barresi mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**
    
    $ gnome-disks
    
    🔹 Baz kardane barname grafiki `gnome-disks`.

    $ gnome-disks /dev/sda
    
    🔹 Baz kardane barname grafiki `gnome-disks` va entekhab disk `/dev/sda` be soorat pishfarz.

✅ **Mesal sade:**
    
    $ gnome-disks
    
    🔹 Ba ejraye in dastoor, panjereye `gnome-disks` baz mishavad va shoma mitavanid etela'ate disk-haye khod ra bebinid va anha ra modiriat konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `gnome-disks` is a graphical utility for managing disks and drives in Linux systems that use Gnome. You can view partitions, format them, mount/unmount them, and check S.M.A.R.T. statuses.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 GUI Based --> Easier for beginner users.
    🔹 LVM Support --> Supports Logical Volume Management
    🔹 S.M.A.R.T. Status Check --> Checks Hard drive S.M.A.R.T. status.

🛠 **Examples:**
    
    $ gnome-disks
    
    🔹 Opens the `gnome-disks` graphical application.

    $ gnome-disks /dev/sda
    
    🔹 Opens the `gnome-disks` graphical application with the `/dev/sda` disk pre-selected.

✅ **Simple Example:**
    
    $ gnome-disks
    
    🔹 Running this command will open the `gnome-disks` window, allowing you to view information about your disks and manage them.
